reviews_data.review_text: I was very sad when Queen City grounds closed so was excited that a new shop had opened in its place. I ordered a large iced coffee with cream and no sugar. What I got was maybe an 8 oz cup of iced coffee- a tiny cup compared to the taller options most coffee shops will serve over ice with a price tag of $5.98. When I questioned the size I was told they were " a specialty coffee shop" as if I was a moron. I took my coffee got halfway down the block and realize it was loaded with sugar so went back and asked if in fact it did have sugar in it. I was told the Barista would need to look as she checked the bottle of the artificial creamer she had doused my iced coffee with. I would like to note that a specialty coffee shop would not ruin coffee with a bunch of sugary artificial creamer.  If you remain in business i suggest you invest in some 1/2&1/2 and large cold drink cups.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thank you for your feedback — we’re sorry your visit was disappointing.
For clarity:
• Our iced coffee is served in a 12oz cup, which is what was provided with your order of iced coffee with cream.
• A splash of sweet cream (no artificial sweeteners) was added as requested.
• When you returned and shared that you did not want any sweetness, our barista apologized, offered to remake the drink, and issued a full refund.
• We do offer half & half upon request and are happy to provide it when specified at the time of ordering.
We maintain professionalism with all our guest and regret that the interaction felt otherwise to you. We aim for a warm and respectful experience that is reciprocal, even when something needs to be corrected.
If you would like to discuss further or give us another opportunity, you are welcome to stop by.

reviews_data.review_text: What an amazing space! So welcoming, friendly people and really great coffee. Highly recommend!

reviews_data.review_text:
UPDATED 10/5/2025 to reflect Indigo's new location:

My food review is based off of coffee — I didn’t have a pastry during this trip.

I did, however, have the best decaf Cardamom Fig latte (which Reba — the owner— ground for me fresh). The quality of my drink was exceptional and the service was impeccable.

Indigo Coffee & Tea is located in the former Queen City Grounds location in Fourth Ward (N. Church Street) and the vibes are soothing. From the playlist and artwork to the furniture in the space and the lighting, this little coffee spot hidden near the heart of  Charlotte is a nice place to meet with friends, work solo, or just hide away.

There is plenty of paid street parking in the area, but you can also park for FREE in the connected parking deck - parking is validated. Street parking is free on Sunday.

It’s one thing to have just amazing customer service all the time. it is another to have that and SPECTACULAR, AMAZING,FLAWLESS DRINKS! Everything about this place is great. REBA AND LISA ARE THE BEST!!!!! Will be back tomorrow!

reviews_data.review_text:
A Calm, Creative Café Worth Returning To

I met a friend here for a meeting and was immediately blown away by the decor. The space gives off an instant sense of calm and, for me, it sparked motivation. After the meeting wrapped, I ended up staying until close to get some work done—and it was the perfect atmosphere for it.

Most cafés can be a little noisy or distracting, but Indigo had just the right hum of productivity, balanced with couples and families coming in for coffee and a snack. During my visit, I had a delicious mocha latte, paired with a blueberry muffin that was moist and satisfying.

Since I stayed so long, I decided to try something else from the menu and ordered an iced fruit tea and it completely surprised me. It was the perfect level of sweetness, super refreshing, and included fresh fruit in every sip. Honestly, I’d go back just for that tea.

Indigo Coffee and Tea has officially been added to my list of go-to work spots. It’s a peaceful, creative space that makes it easy to focus while still enjoying the energy of a well-loved café. I’ll be back.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi.  Thank you for your business and I hope you are able to come visit us at our new location.  Hope to see you soon!  Thank you!

Most cafés can be a little noisy or distracting, but Indigo had just the right hum of productivity, balanced with couples and families coming in for coffee and a snack. During my visit, I had a delicious mocha latte, paired with a blueberry muffin that was moist and satisfying.

Since I stayed so long, I decided to try something else from the menu and ordered an iced fruit tea and it completely surprised me. It was the perfect level of sweetness, super refreshing, and included fresh fruit in every sip. Honestly, I’d go back just for that tea.

Indigo Coffee and Tea has officially been added to my list of go-to work spots. It’s a peaceful, creative space that makes it easy to focus while still enjoying the energy of a well-loved café. I’ll be back.
